Dialogue: 10,0:00:35.01,0:00:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:37.26,0:00:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Start!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.27,0:00:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Giulia! Good start! {it is "Giulia" in https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inochi_No_Chikyuu:_Dioxin_No_Natsu - maybe it's the italian spelling, might replace but no big deal}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.68,0:00:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking good, Lucio! \NYou've almost caught her!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:45.10,0:00:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother! Go for it!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.91,0:01:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even a ten-meter\N handicap could help me!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:04.46,0:01:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't compete with you at all!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:07.83,0:01:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's nothing new. You couldn't compete with me in a million years.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:11.92,0:01:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Giulia.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.72,0:01:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new personal record. Look!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:17.01,0:01:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay! I did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:19.14,0:01:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Giulia! You broke\N your record on your birthday!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:23.89,0:01:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Giulia!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:31.86,0:01:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Giulia! Congratulations!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:34.90,0:01:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Enrico, Lucio.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.49,0:01:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Maria, Angelo.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.62,0:01:44.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,My name is Giuliana Bianchi. {again, Giuliana "Giulia" Bianchi in https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inochi_No_Chikyuu:_Dioxin_No_Natsu}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:44.29,0:01:48.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,Today, July 10th, was the start\N of summer vacation.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.12,0:01:50.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,Right on my 11th birthday!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.46,0:01:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for waiting!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.46,0:01:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, amazing!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.71,0:01:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks totally delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.67,0:01:57.38,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yummy, looks great! {NIG}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.93,0:02:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mama and I made\N this cake together.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.89,0:02:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I helped too!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.93,0:02:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Marco helped us by putting on the candles.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.18,0:02:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. All eleven of them.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.46,0:02:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 12:30 already?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.38,0:02:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonio and Anna sure are late. {okay, here's what https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inochi_No_Chikyuu:_Dioxin_No_Natsu has to say about it: "His older brother, Tonio, is the veterinarian of Seveso, as well as the husband of Anna, Giulia's sister." - apparently Lucio and Giulia are not relatives, but just school friends and their older siblings are a pair, let's remember that, Giulia big sister is Anna and little brother is Marco}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.30,0:02:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they come soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.72,0:02:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My stomach is growling.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.18,0:02:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Same here.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.05,0:02:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear! Dear!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.85,0:02:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.06,0:02:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonio just called from the hospital.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.85,0:02:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,From the hospital?\NSomething happened to him?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.02,0:02:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say that, \Nbecause Anna is expecting a child!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.19,0:02:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna is expecting a baby?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.11,0:03:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Is that true, Milena?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.24,0:03:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He said she's in her second month.\NShe'll give birth next spring!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.99,0:03:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? So I'm becoming\N a grandpa soon?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.16,0:03:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Everyone, let's celebrate!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.63,0:03:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.55,0:03:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To celebrate Giulia's birthday, \Nand Anna and Tonio's child...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.68,0:03:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.25,0:03:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell is that?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.05,0:04:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this powder?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.23,0:04:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That cloud looks like it'll be here soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.07,0:05:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind is blowing it this way.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.70,0:05:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this stench?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.20,0:05:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It smells like chlorine.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.20,0:05:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, get inside the house, now!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.84,0:05:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Leo, come with me!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.75,0:05:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Milena, Giulia, shut the windows tight! {lit is "below/downwards windows" so can't be sure he means basement}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.80,0:05:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Leon, come to me, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.18,0:05:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria, hurry up!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.97,0:05:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.31,0:05:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.32,0:05:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What could this be?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.99,0:05:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, but I feel like\N something terrible has happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.54,0:05:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Тоnio!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.50,0:06:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.75,0:06:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna, are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.55,0:06:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My eyes are burning!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.76,0:06:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna! Anna!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.85,0:06:18.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,Not long after that, the white powder stopped falling from the sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.94,0:06:23.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,Not even a single cicada{/cricket} was chirping. \NEverything was silent and white.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.44,0:06:25.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was an eerie sight.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.78,0:06:37.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,The next morning, the thick layer of white powder had nearly disappeared.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.21,0:06:45.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, in the sky to the southeast, \Nan ominous gray cloud still floated eerily.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.38,0:06:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Mom.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.72,0:06:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning. Giulia, look at this. \NI picked them just now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.39,0:06:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all covered with some kind of oily film.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.52,0:06:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What a pity.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.02,0:07:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to take them to Anna\N when I visit her later.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.90,0:07:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Visit her?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.40,0:07:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She felt poorly and was very sleepy.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.44,0:07:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But she now has a baby inside her, \Nso I'm worried sick.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.36,0:07:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was that white powder?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.07,0:07:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps. I can't be sure,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.66,0:07:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but Tonio complained about a headache\N before going to work.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.33,0:07:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, take me with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.50,0:07:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm worried about Anna.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.63,0:07:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.17,0:07:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Marco, weren't you going\N to the pool today?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.47,0:07:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go after we come back from Anna's.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.93,0:07:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.23,0:07:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a bit of a headache too.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.85,0:07:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.11,0:07:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My eyes hurt a little.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.98,0:07:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it's because of that white powder, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.41,0:07:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.95,0:07:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's Anna's mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.83,0:08:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, Grandma Sonia!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.91,0:08:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.21,0:08:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Anna?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.46,0:08:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. My headache and the pain in my eyes\Nhave subsided a lot.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.84,0:08:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? I'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.68,0:08:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonio can't get any rest because\N he's so busy at the vet clinic.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.35,0:08:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma Sonia really helped us out \Nby agreeing to look after me.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.43,0:08:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.39,0:08:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No need. Anna and I are neighbors.\NIt's only natural.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.31,0:08:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, eat a lot today,\N and have a good rest.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.44,0:08:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't let it affect the child in your belly.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.07,0:08:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. Now's the most crucial period for its development.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.95,0:08:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.67,0:08:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready! Start!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.05,0:08:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.88,0:08:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Run, Giulia!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.73,0:09:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Giulia?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.69,0:09:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My eyes still hurt,\N and my stamina is gone.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.15,0:09:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you shouldn't\N force yourself for now?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.53,0:09:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.32,0:09:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's call it a day.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.53,0:09:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, any idea where Enrico is?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.58,0:09:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really unusual for him not to be here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.00,0:09:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's busy with something?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.42,0:09:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go to our usual hangout for now.\N Maybe he'll join us later.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.76,0:09:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That one!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.76,0:09:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Whoa! It looks delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.27,0:09:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, maybe we should peel the plums\N before eating them?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.19,0:09:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. There's some sort of oily sheen on them.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.53,0:10:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's because of the white powder?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.07,0:10:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.91,0:10:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wipe it off, and it'll be safe to eat.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:07.62,0:10:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yummy!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.04,0:10:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I'd rather eat it peeled.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.05,0:10:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That cloud's still there.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.51,0:10:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes me uneasy, somehow.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.97,0:10:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.18,0:10:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It will disperse when the wind picks up. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.43,0:10:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stop worrying, \Neven if you tell me to!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.77,0:10:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My stepsister's body went haywire \Nafter she got showered with that powder.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.86,0:10:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what could that powder have been?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.28,0:10:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, have you heard?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.36,0:10:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the white powder fell
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.78,0:10:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because of an accident at the ICMESA plant, \Nabout two kilometers north of here.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:44.45,0:10:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The ICMESA plant?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.20,0:10:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The newspaper had\N a small story about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.21,0:10:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What were they producing at that plant?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.67,0:10:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Some chemicals, apparently,\N but I couldn't tell which ones.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.30,0:10:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.17,0:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrico's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.05,0:11:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys, you mustn't eat those plums!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.47,0:11:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.51,0:11:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Some guys from the Health Department​{/health care center; health care centre} \Ncame to see my dad in his office.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.69,0:11:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I overheard a bit of their conversation.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.56,0:11:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you on Sunday.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.69,0:11:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.23,0:11:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Health Department has been swamped\N with inquiries from local people, Mayor Carlo.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.16,0:11:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then give me all the details about the accident at the ICMESA plant.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.49,0:11:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The ICMESA plant is owned by a company called Givaudan, based in Switzerland.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.54,0:11:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In turn, Givaudan is a subsidiary of the Hoffmann-La Roche company.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.59,0:11:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Roche is a multinational conglomerate that makes pharmaceuticals and pesticides, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.93,0:11:43.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,Roche?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.01,0:11:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as we know, the ICMESA plant was producing a chemical called TCP.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.77,0:11:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,TCP?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.27,0:11:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The full name is trichlorophenol.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.90,0:12:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's used in the production of perfumes, cosmetics, surgical antiseptic, and so on.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.24,0:12:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The chemical reaction used to make it\N caused yesterday's accident.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.20,0:12:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's likely that the compound\N released into the air was TCP.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.91,0:12:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even though TCP \Nis a powerful irritant,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.00,0:12:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,able to cause temporary\N headaches and eye pain,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.13,0:12:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we believe it has\N no other harmful effects.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.67,0:12:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Well, that's the first comforting news today.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.05,0:12:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you both for letting me know.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.06,0:12:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So they say the headache and burning eyes are only temporary?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.52,0:12:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,See now? There's no reason \Nto worry at all!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.11,0:12:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.11,0:12:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as the Health guys left,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.24,0:12:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,some top executives from the ICMESA plant came to see my dad.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.32,0:12:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Executives?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.33,0:12:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't help worrying\N about what they said.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.16,0:12:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We've sent samples of what fell on Seveso to Roche HQ in Switzerland.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.75,0:13:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the analysis is available,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.71,0:13:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd like you to discourage the residents of Seveso
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.63,0:13:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from eating locally grown fruits, \Nvegetables, and the like.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.80,0:13:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying that eating plants affected by that powder is harmful to people?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.31,0:13:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't say that, exactly.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.69,0:13:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, Mr. Mayor, even if\N we find it's totally harmless,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.32,0:13:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you can never be too cautious.\N As they say, better safe than sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.70,0:13:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear you.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.45,0:13:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Please notify me immediately\N when the results of the analysis are available.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.00,0:13:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's not quite right here.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.75,0:13:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.88,0:13:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They say that TCP does no harm,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.84,0:13:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,yet they don't want us to eat local produce?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.38,0:13:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.84,0:13:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, why don't we try to find out for sure\Nby going to the ICMESA plant together?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.73,0:13:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Find out for sure?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.39,0:13:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll sneak into the plant, secretly.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.85,0:14:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting here and fretting\Nwon't get us anywhere.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.57,0:14:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Giulia, say what you want, but that's obviously going too far. Right, guys?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.94,0:14:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I agree with Giulia.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.82,0:14:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's worth looking into.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.83,0:14:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.58,0:14:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We may learn the truth \N if we go to the site.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.16,0:14:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, Maria?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.21,0:14:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come too. Better that than worrying.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.34,0:14:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what about you, Angelo? \NAre you in or out?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.63,0:14:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, fine. I'll come too.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.80,0:14:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! Then the ICMESA accident\N investigation team is ready to go!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.89,0:14:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.78,0:14:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, how do we sneak in?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.07,0:14:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it to me. I have just the plan for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.49,0:14:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you didn't wanna come in the first place?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.37,0:14:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm committed to doing it right.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.62,0:15:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's your plan?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.04,0:15:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria and I will try to distract that guy, somehow,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.09,0:15:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,while you, Lucio, and Giulia sneak in.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.21,0:15:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think I can.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.68,0:15:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I'll do the talking.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.30,0:15:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, sir?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.26,0:15:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.52,0:15:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We seem to have lost our way.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.85,0:15:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were you going?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.19,0:15:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The northern train station in Seveso. \NIt's supposed to be this way.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.27,0:15:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.69,0:15:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then. You start here \Nand pass by two traffic lights.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.69,0:15:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then turn right and walk for 200 meters.\NOn the street corner, you'll see a school.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.30,0:15:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly remembered where it is! \NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.87,0:15:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.58,0:15:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, it's a mighty strange thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.67,0:15:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The guys managing this place flatly refuse \Nto explain what the hell happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.05,0:15:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they take us workers for?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.01,0:15:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The big shots who own it\N are hiding their dirty laundry.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.18,0:16:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They think it's okay to dump the chemicals they're making into the plant's wastewater.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.86,0:16:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what they're doing.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.82,0:16:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They seem to be wiping up\N the white powder that fell yesterday.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.69,0:16:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I still can't believe it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.15,0:16:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The pressure in the heated reactor over there\N got so high that the safety valve blew.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.45,0:16:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It was left unattended and overheated badly.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.38,0:16:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "The heated reactor"?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.30,0:16:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's in that building?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.67,0:16:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.89,0:16:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! It's huge!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.19,0:16:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the reactor \Nthat caused the accident?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.19,0:16:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are piles of white powder on it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.65,0:16:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! There's a hole over there!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.32,0:16:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be where that cloud came from.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.86,0:16:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.99,0:17:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:03.37,0:17:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Will Enrico and the others be okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.50,0:17:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria, Enrico is the only thing\N on your mind lately.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.63,0:17:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.68,0:17:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those guys up to?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.31,0:17:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are they going?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.56,0:17:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's follow them.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.02,0:17:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:26.90,0:17:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you sneaked in here to find out more about the accident that happened yesterday, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:32.03,0:17:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Some of the things I heard\N about it were really worrying.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.45,0:17:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Like what?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.91,0:17:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the plant managers were\N discussing it with the mayor?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.96,0:17:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Why would they first say that TCP is harmless,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.50,0:17:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but then forbid eating local produce?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.75,0:17:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think that's odd?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.05,0:17:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt fishy to me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.26,0:18:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They're hiding something about this plant.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.93,0:18:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.68,0:18:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When the accident had just happened...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.99,0:18:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone! Hurry home at once \Nand take a shower!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.36,0:18:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, what just happened here?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.28,0:18:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this white powder on all of us?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.20,0:18:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know yet!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:25.58,0:18:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll explain later, but for now, just go home! Got that?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.08,0:18:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't like him to be that flustered.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.38,0:18:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately after the incident, Roche sent\N a team of soil technicians to the area.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.14,0:18:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Soil technicians?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.23,0:18:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.77,0:18:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:50.85,0:18:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go ask.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.90,0:18:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait, Angelo!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.86,0:18:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.37,0:19:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're working?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.20,0:19:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Uh, I'm sending soil\N samples to Switzerland.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.99,0:19:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you sending them to Switzerland?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.00,0:19:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So they can be analyzed at Hoffman-La Roche.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.12,0:19:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! We're supposed to keep our mouths shut, even with kids!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.04,0:19:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.59,0:19:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very busy. Off you go.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.09,0:19:21.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hoffmann-La Roche?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.14,0:19:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. You can leave this way\N without anyone noticing.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.23,0:19:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.35,0:19:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was a close call. \NDon't risk coming here again.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.73,0:19:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Vito.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.65,0:19:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need more info, \NI'll tell you what I know.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.61,0:19:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Come see me at this address.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.20,0:19:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.20,0:19:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? So this guy Vito helped you,\N just like that?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.54,0:19:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.58,0:19:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Vito also thinks something fishy's going on at the plant.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.58,0:19:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.75,0:19:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all the way out here?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.01,0:20:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they the soil technicians that Vito mentioned?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.80,0:20:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.22,0:20:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does their headquarters need so many samples from here? {lit: what will the HQ do with everything they collected and sent from here}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.18,0:20:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Vito and his guys don't know either.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.64,0:20:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing we know for sure. The plant managers are hiding something big.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.74,0:20:23.82,TV,,0,0,0,,And now, a special bulletin.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.82,0:20:27.03,TV,,0,0,0,,New details about yesterday's accident at the ICMESA plant
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.03,0:20:30.70,TV,,0,0,0,,indicate that the leaked chemical was probably a substance called TCP.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.37,0:20:33.08,TV,,0,0,0,,There is no cause for concern,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.08,0:20:35.83,TV,,0,0,0,,but as a precaution,\N pending further investigation,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:35.83,0:20:38.92,TV,,0,0,0,,residents should not eat locally grown fruit or vegetables.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.38,0:20:40.21,TV,,0,0,0,,I repeat...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.21,0:20:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,"As a precaution?" What does that mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.93,0:20:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.68,0:20:54.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,The next day, that ominous cloud \Nwas no longer looming in the sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:55.23,0:20:58.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,Apparently, a strong wind off the Alps blew it away.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:18.13,0:21:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any injuries.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.26,0:21:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Mayor, you have a business call \Nfrom the Hoffmann-La Roche company.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.77,0:21:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,From Roche?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.27,0:21:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was flapping frantically, \Nand then it fell down.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.25,0:22:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria! Hang on! Maria!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.84,0:22:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?! \NThe white powder was toxic?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:10.85,0:22:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. After extensive analysis \Nat Roche laboratories,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.81,0:22:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we've established that the powder
Dialogue: 10,0:22:15.64,0:22:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,contained small quantities\N of an extremely toxic substance.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:19.76,0:22:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What substance is that, exactly?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:22.73,0:22:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We aren't sure yet. We have just started analyzing the first set of samples.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:27.49,0:22:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we've received more test results,\N we'll contact you again.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:35.87,0:22:39.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,What was this "extremely toxic substance" they were talking about?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:39.56,0:22:41.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,How will it affect people?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:41.88,0:22:47.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,Still, if I release a vague statement,\N the town will descend into panic.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:53.10,0:22:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,God, what should I do now?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:59.52,0:23:03.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,The next day, we gathered at Maria's house.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:04.40,0:23:07.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,She called us over because Leo was acting strangely.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:09.57,0:23:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He became very ill yesterday, quite suddenly.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:13.24,0:23:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been unable to eat ever since.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:15.83,0:23:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Maria, you should take him to my brother Tonio's vet clinic for a checkup.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:20.46,0:23:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good idea, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:23.25,0:23:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:25.05,0:23:29.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,The vet clinic was full of animals\N that had suddenly become very sick.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.73,0:23:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He's suffering from acute organ failure. \NI can't do anything more for him.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.44,0:23:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this happening to Leon?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.02,0:23:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to know myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.32,0:23:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the animals I've seen today \Nare suffering from the same symptoms.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.16,0:23:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, can't you do anything at all?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.49,0:24:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only shorten his suffering \Nby giving him a peaceful death.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.62,0:24:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Not that! I can't let Leon die! Never!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:05.17,0:24:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria...
Dialogue: 10,0:24:15.26,0:24:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Leon, I'm sorry. Leon!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:19.85,0:24:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This was beyond your control, Maria.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:23.23,0:24:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now animals are dropping dead in droves.\NWhat the hell is going on here?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:31.49,0:24:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find out.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:33.57,0:24:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting around will get us nowhere!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:35.91,0:24:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll form a detective team\N and find out what's really going on here!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:41.00,0:24:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A detective team?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:42.75,0:24:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I like the idea.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:43.67,0:24:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help you too. I won't sleep a wink until I know what happened to Leon!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:49.92,0:24:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help too, Giulia.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:52.59,0:24:56.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,And that's how we started\N the Seveso Detective Team.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:03.85,0:25:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so hot! And the AC finally conked out.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.02,0:25:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had my fill of this junker.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:10.11,0:25:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, they send me to cover\N an accident at a rural chemical plant.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:13.53,0:25:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really out of luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:15.91,0:25:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And later this evening, I have to cover\N a fashion show in Milan.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:19.58,0:25:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously! My boss sure is a slave driver.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:36.51,0:25:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you poor thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:39.43,0:25:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it's your own fault. You should know better than to fly into a car's windscreen.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:59.82,0:26:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dead.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:12.30,0:26:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:15.59,0:26:17.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,Ten days after the accident,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:17.51,0:26:20.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,we heard that Grandma Sonia\N was in the hospital.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:20.97,0:26:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, only my eyes and head hurt,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:24.43,0:26:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but now I also have a rash\N on my hands and feet.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:26.89,0:26:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My belly is swollen too, \Nand I have trouble walking.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:30.19,0:26:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, what do the doctors think?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:33.02,0:26:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctors believe I may be suffering \Nfrom some acute allergic reaction.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:38.03,0:26:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, it has nothing to do \Nwith the white powder?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:41.53,0:26:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think anyone knows for sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:44.54,0:26:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my... So they can't\N even establish a cause?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:48.75,0:26:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate your concern, Anna.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.63,0:26:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm worried about you, dear,\Nfar more than about me.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:55.13,0:26:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your baby doing well?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.38,0:26:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:58.47,0:27:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. I'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:06.72,0:27:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So this rash appeared on your face on the second or third day after the white powder fell?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:11.90,0:27:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. In addition, I feel nauseous and have a headache.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:15.28,0:27:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly everyone here today \Nhas the very same symptoms.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:23.83,0:27:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how it is?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:33.84,0:27:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, one moment, please.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:36.63,0:27:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:37.88,0:27:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you mind showing me the way \Nto the ICMESA plant?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:41.34,0:27:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The plant was shut down two days ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:43.93,0:27:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Shut down?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:46.39,0:27:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The mayor ordered the plant closed \Nuntil the end of the investigation.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:50.48,0:27:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What a pity.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:52.60,0:27:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, did you have business with that plant?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:55.69,0:28:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Actually, I'm a reporter for the Italian branch of a Japanese newspaper.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:05.45,0:28:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ando Shiro.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:08.54,0:28:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I was sent here to cover\N the accident the other day.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.75,0:28:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I'm in a bind...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:14.00,0:28:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I write an article if I can't get information about the plant?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:19.30,0:28:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! You could interview Vito instead.{false i-frame}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:22.51,0:28:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Vito?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:23.68,0:28:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a worker at the ICMESA Plant. \NHe was there when it happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:28.16,0:28:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Right there?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:29.22,0:28:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:34.98,0:28:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you tell me\N how the incident unfolded?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:38.98,0:28:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The heated tank that housed\N the chemicals for producing TCP
Dialogue: 10,0:28:42.45,0:28:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,had a safety valve on it, \Nto prevent the tank from exploding.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:46.37,0:28:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the temperature got high enough,\N the valve opened,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:49.37,0:28:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,blowing the tank's contents into the air.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:52.54,0:28:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the normal temperature range for the tank?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:57.21,0:29:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, it's between 140 and 170 Celsius.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:01.51,0:29:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then do you know what tank temperature would cause the safety valve to blow?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:07.10,0:29:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The safety valve wouldn't release\Nunless the temperature reached 320 degrees.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:13.89,0:29:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the temperature inside must have been at least 320 degrees?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:18.69,0:29:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Actually, when the temperature in the tank gets too high,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:22.61,0:29:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a cooling system kicks in automatically,\N knocking the temperature back down.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:27.41,0:29:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But it didn't work, for some reason?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:30.29,0:29:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Our site operators\N had to start it manually.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:40.92,0:29:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Right afterward, we were told to go home\N immediately and take a shower.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:45.05,0:29:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But nobody would give us an explanation\N about what was going on.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:50.22,0:29:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We believe that the big company\N behind this must be hiding something.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:54.23,0:29:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, what was the ultimate purpose of making TCP?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:58.60,0:30:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't fully understand it myself,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:00.73,0:30:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think it's used to make herbicides and surgical antiseptic.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:05.53,0:30:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Herbicides?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:08.32,0:30:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I was hired at the plant,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:10.33,0:30:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard it was used as a defoliant\N during the Vietnam War.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:15.20,0:30:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A defoliant? Like "Agent Orange"? {no clue what's sakusen here, usually it'd be operation/strategy}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:20.71,0:30:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me! I can't go\N to the fashion show tonight!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:24.38,0:30:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:25.38,0:30:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:26.38,0:30:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard that before, boss! \NI understand we're short-staffed.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:29.51,0:30:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Seveso accident is far more serious!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:32.14,0:30:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, I can't leave here, period!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:35.81,0:30:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it all!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:39.44,0:30:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ando, maybe you should cover your next story?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:42.65,0:30:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:44.78,0:30:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just my intuition,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:46.57,0:30:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but during the accident,\N more than just TCP fell on the town.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:51.95,0:30:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a feeling that something\N more toxic was mixed in with it.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:56.79,0:30:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Something more toxic?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:58.71,0:31:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What could {\i1}that{\i0} be?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:00.79,0:31:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,To find out, we'll need to consult an expert.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:05.42,0:31:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! There's a Galileo Research Institute in Milan.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:08.72,0:31:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a world-renowned\N bio-medical research lab.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:12.22,0:31:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get them involved, \Nwe might learn something.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:14.93,0:31:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:15.72,0:31:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go ask them right away.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:18.10,0:31:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, get in the car.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:23.06,0:31:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ando!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:26.94,0:31:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Mr. Ando?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:29.20,0:31:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine. This happens to me all the time.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:32.16,0:31:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, if they're all that renowned,\N will they listen to what we want to ask?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:40.29,0:31:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:42.42,0:31:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We shouldn't expect them\N to conduct an investigation
Dialogue: 10,0:31:45.56,0:31:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,at the request of an unknown\N journalist like me.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:49.67,0:31:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's ask the mayor to do it for us!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:52.43,0:31:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The mayor?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:53.97,0:31:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrico, we're counting on you!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:58.60,0:32:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:00.81,0:32:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My, if it isn't Enrico. Hello.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:03.19,0:32:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got something urgent I need\N to discuss with my father.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:06.73,0:32:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I go see him now?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:08.11,0:32:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He doesn't have any appointments right now, so it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:12.57,0:32:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The mayor is in his office.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:14.32,0:32:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Guys, this way!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:19.25,0:32:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:19.70,0:32:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:21.62,0:32:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 10,0:32:22.87,0:32:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:28.92,0:32:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:31.76,0:32:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrico?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:36.14,0:32:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, I'm sorry to barge in like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:38.72,0:32:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What brings you here\N with all of your friends?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:42.60,0:32:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And who exactly is {\i1}this{\i0} man?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:45.65,0:32:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I work for the Italian branch of a Japanese newspaper.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:49.23,0:32:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Ando Shiro.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:51.07,0:32:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here to write about the recent accident.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:55.28,0:32:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what can I do for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:57.70,0:33:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,About that... We have a favor to ask you, as the mayor.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:00.87,0:33:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted you to ask\N the Galileo Institute of Milan
Dialogue: 10,0:33:04.00,0:33:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to examine the white powder\N that fell on Seveso.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:07.46,0:33:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No. If that's what interests you,
Dialogue: 10,0:33:09.84,0:33:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll be informed of all\N the details before long.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:13.72,0:33:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Roche has been uncooperative about sharing their results,
Dialogue: 10,0:33:18.10,0:33:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so I've sent my attorney to ask their executives about the situation personally.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:22.23,0:33:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How long will it take? {When will this happen?}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:24.10,0:33:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Not long.{/happening right now}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:25.69,0:33:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as the analysis results arrive, \NI will make an announcement.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:29.44,0:33:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I suggest you\N return home for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:34.70,0:33:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrico, you and your friends should go too.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:39.37,0:33:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:42.66,0:33:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You really think that Roche will tell your attorney the truth about this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:47.71,0:33:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, we're the only\N ones after the truth!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:50.09,0:33:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Institute is in the best\N position to help with that!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:53.55,0:33:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And the sooner, the better!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:56.43,0:33:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:33:57.51,0:34:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad! Small animals are dropping dead one after another.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:02.89,0:34:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Birds, chickens, cats, dogs!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:06.85,0:34:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At Lucio's brother's clinic,\N they've had to put them all down
Dialogue: 10,0:34:09.62,0:34:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because there was nothing\N else they could do!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:14.57,0:34:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you think will be next?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:18.57,0:34:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,People!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:31.46,0:34:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it, Enrico.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:33.92,0:34:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask the Institute to look into it.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:40.85,0:34:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right, Professor Marella.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:43.43,0:34:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The plant confirmed that the main component of the released material was TCP.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:48.52,0:34:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'd like to know \Nif it was {\i1}only{\i0} TCP.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:51.44,0:34:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'd like to find out whether anything other than TCP was released?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:56.07,0:34:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. By the way, according\N to a worker at the plant,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:58.90,0:35:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of the accident, the temperature\N inside the reactor exceeded 320 degrees.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:05.16,0:35:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:06.50,0:35:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll look into it right away and call you if I discover anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:11.50,0:35:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Exceeded 320 degrees?
Dialogue: 10,0:35:17.34,0:35:19.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,And then, ten minutes later...
Dialogue: 10,0:35:21.89,0:35:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. Professor Marella?\NAh... One moment, please.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:26.14,0:35:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mayor! Please pick up the other phone and listen with me!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:30.35,0:35:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,After reviewing the information you provided,\N I have found something terrible.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:48.45,0:35:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Dioxin?
Dialogue: 10,0:35:49.62,0:35:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:50.92,0:35:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The TCP powder{added} that fell on Seveso was mixed with a substance called dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:56.88,0:35:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is this "dioxin" stuff?
Dialogue: 10,0:35:59.22,0:36:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a byproduct of a runaway reaction that starts when TCP is heated above 200 degrees Celsius.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:05.26,0:36:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of the accident, \Nthe reactor hit 320 degrees.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:08.43,0:36:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no doubt that \Nsome dioxin must've been produced.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:12.56,0:36:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reason why animals are dying and people are feeling sick is this dioxin?
Dialogue: 10,0:36:18.61,0:36:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Dioxin is much more poisonous than TCP, \N to an almost incomprehensible degree.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:26.41,0:36:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Mr. Ando, there's no need\N to get so excited!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:31.50,0:36:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But did he say anything about {\i1}how{\i0} poisonous this dioxin is? {lit: this toxicity of dioxing you're talking about, how much is that thing?}
Dialogue: 10,0:36:36.38,0:36:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Professor Marella,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:38.25,0:36:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,if you mixed a kilogram of food with just one gram of TCP and fed it to rabbits,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:42.84,0:36:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,half of those rabbits would die soon after.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:47.22,0:36:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But dioxin is poisonous on a different scale.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:50.35,0:36:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It would only take one part in a hundred million to kill as many rabbits.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:56.02,0:36:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,One part in a hundred million?
Dialogue: 10,0:36:58.69,0:37:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's so crazy, I can't even imagine it.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:01.74,0:37:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then here's a simpler explanation.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:04.32,0:37:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Dioxin is about a thousand times\N more toxic than {potassium }cyanide.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:08.49,0:37:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not as fast acting as cyanide,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:10.91,0:37:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but eventually, one gram would be enough \Nto kill 830,000 guinea pigs.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:15.17,0:37:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,One gram would kill 830,000?!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:17.71,0:37:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people would that kill?
Dialogue: 10,0:37:20.34,0:37:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Nobody would dare\N perform an experiment like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:24.51,0:37:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:30.35,0:37:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you no-good hunk of junk!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:32.52,0:37:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you break down right now?!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:34.98,0:37:38.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Mayor's attorney won't get\N anything useful out of Roche.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:38.81,0:37:41.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,They'll just skirt around the truth.\N We have to hurry.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:43.49,0:37:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ando! Can I help you somehow?
Dialogue: 10,0:37:47.36,0:37:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need. Better change into the clothes we borrowed.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:50.74,0:37:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the use of Enrico putting on the mayor's suit?
Dialogue: 10,0:37:54.25,0:37:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't catch up with the attorney, then Enrico and I will barge in.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:08.09,0:38:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What? The meeting with the President has already begun?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:11.93,0:38:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:12.89,0:38:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I showed the mayor's attorney to the President's office just a little while ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:17.44,0:38:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn, we didn't make it in time.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:19.73,0:38:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Would you please {urgently }direct us \Nto the President's office as well?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:24.86,0:38:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Excuse me, but with whom do I have the honor of speaking?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:28.45,0:38:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the son of Silvio Carlo,\N the mayor of Seveso. Enrico Carlo.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:36.41,0:38:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Enrico's all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:38.75,0:38:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be fine. Besides, he's got Mr. Ando with him.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:42.00,0:38:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Lucio?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:43.63,0:38:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:47.13,0:38:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrico, we're meeting\N Roche's big shots now.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:50.09,0:38:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Show them you're no pushover.\NTake the fight head-on.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:52.68,0:38:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:57.88,0:38:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Are you okay, Mr. Ando?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:59.85,0:39:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I'm fine...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:03.19,0:39:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming\N out of your way to meet us.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:08.57,0:39:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President, well, Seveso's mayor...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:12.16,0:39:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for being late.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:14.45,0:39:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you gentlemen?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:16.79,0:39:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the son of the mayor of Seveso, Enrico Carlo.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:21.04,0:39:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My father ordered me \Nto be present at the meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:28.17,0:39:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Rudolf Söll{just "zeru" in credits so anything would do, current spelling seems alright to me - Perevodildo}, \NChairman of Hoffmann-La Roche.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:34.31,0:39:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am Don Partfogel.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:36.60,0:39:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I am president of Givaudan,\N the parent company of the ICMESA plant.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:42.40,0:39:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Mr. Ando Shiro.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:44.11,0:39:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A consulting journalist.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:46.86,0:39:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A journalist{, you say}?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:50.53,0:39:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:59.37,0:40:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, regarding the incident...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:01.83,0:40:04.04,Overlap,,0,0,0,,So, can you tell us...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:04.04,0:40:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,how much dioxin was blown into the air\N over Seveso as a result of the accident?
Dialogue: 10,0:40:11.76,0:40:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We don't know.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:13.55,0:40:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As we've said, our investigation\N is still underway.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:17.97,0:40:21.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,I see. So they {\i0}did{\i1} know\N about the dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:22.19,0:40:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:24.61,0:40:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If you measured the amount of TCP inside the reactor at the time of the accident,
Dialogue: 10,0:40:28.82,0:40:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you should've been able\N to make an initial estimate.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:31.70,0:40:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No, even making an estimate like that would be difficult.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:35.20,0:40:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, we don't know the temperature\N in the reactor at the time of the accident.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:39.41,0:40:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:40.79,0:40:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no secret that the reactor's safety valve can handle temperatures up to 320 degrees.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:45.92,0:40:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I know that much.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:48.00,0:40:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone in your position {\i1}must{\i0} know this.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:50.46,0:40:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:51.47,0:40:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Using 320 degrees as a lower limit,\N you can make a crude estimate.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:57.38,0:41:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right if you're unable to answer us.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:00.68,0:41:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We can make the calculations ourselves \Nand publish them in the morning news.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:04.69,0:41:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've already gone that far, \Nit's out of our hands.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:07.94,0:41:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We were cautious about publishing crude numbers from superficial calculations.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:14.28,0:41:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But we estimate that two or three kilograms\N of dioxin were released into the environment.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:20.62,0:41:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one gram of this dioxin \Ncan kill 830,000 guinea pigs.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:25.75,0:41:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you released two or three {\i1}kilograms{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:27.84,0:41:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you even imagine how many people that amount will harm?!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:32.17,0:41:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You! You knew these facts all along, but you hid them from everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:36.43,0:41:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a blatant criminal act, if you ask me!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:39.14,0:41:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be so sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:40.72,0:41:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When the results from analyzing\N the first samples arrived on July 14th,
Dialogue: 10,0:41:45.27,0:41:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we informed the mayor that the white powder was mixed with an extremely dangerous toxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:53.86,0:41:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot credit or blame us
Dialogue: 10,0:41:55.90,0:42:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for the measures the mayor did or did not take in response to this information.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:01.74,0:42:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 10,0:42:03.58,0:42:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,my father knew all along that the powder contained a powerful toxin,
Dialogue: 10,0:42:07.62,0:42:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but he decided to keep it a secret?
Dialogue: 10,0:42:10.71,0:42:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That was our assumption as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:17.43,0:42:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:42:19.64,0:42:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:24.60,0:42:29.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,{\t(4200,5000,\c&HDACDD2&\3c&HDACDD2&)}After Enrico told his father about the meeting,\N Mayor Carlo set to work at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:30.61,0:42:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The TCP released during the accident at the ICMESA plant
Dialogue: 10,0:42:33.69,0:42:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was mixed with an extremely toxic substance called dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:40.16,0:42:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Residents of Seveso, you must not eat vegetables or fruits grown in the area, no matter what.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:45.37,0:42:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, please watch for further instructions.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:49.96,0:42:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Dioxin?
Dialogue: 10,0:42:54.46,0:42:59.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,Through the mass media, Mayor Carlo declared a state of emergency in Seveso.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:59.89,0:43:04.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,He immediately set up an emergency team to counter the threat of dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:04.35,0:43:07.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,He also assembled a council of scientists, led by Professor Marella,
Dialogue: 10,0:43:07.76,0:43:10.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,who got to work without delay on analyzing dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:10.35,0:43:12.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,He worked tirelessly, with no breaks.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:13.73,0:43:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:16.40,0:43:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? It's you, Enrico?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:19.03,0:43:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, I brought you a change of clothes.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:21.62,0:43:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you so much.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:26.83,0:43:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be coming home\N anytime soon, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:30.54,0:43:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm waiting for reports\N on the degree of contamination.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:34.04,0:43:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll come up with a plan for countermeasures.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:36.59,0:43:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell your mom I won't be coming home for two or three days.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:40.88,0:43:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 10,0:43:46.22,0:43:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:48.56,0:43:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You should take care of yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:51.52,0:43:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:57.57,0:43:59.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,That means... my father...
Dialogue: 10,0:43:59.61,0:44:03.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,knew all along that the powder contained a powerful toxin,
Dialogue: 10,0:44:03.20,0:44:06.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,but he decided to keep it a secret?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:06.49,0:44:09.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,That was our assumption as well.{42:10}
Dialogue: 10,0:44:15.38,0:44:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what my mom said. We can't see the white powder anymore,
Dialogue: 10,0:44:19.21,0:44:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so it means the dioxin\N must have disappeared.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:21.72,0:44:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been told that yesterday's downpour\N washed away all the dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:27.26,0:44:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we're out of the woods already, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:30.68,0:44:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really sure about that?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:33.19,0:44:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:34.06,0:44:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ando!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:35.02,0:44:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky I came across you.\NYou guys wanna come with me?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:39.08,0:44:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:40.99,0:44:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,To see Professor Marella.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:42.99,0:44:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to ask him for more details about dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:47.53,0:44:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So dioxin has no color or taste?
Dialogue: 10,0:44:54.04,0:44:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. And dioxin doesn't disappear, \Neven if it's washed away by the rain.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:59.17,0:45:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It remains soaked into the soil.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:01.63,0:45:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's still everywhere around us, \Neven if we can't see it?
Dialogue: 10,0:45:06.30,0:45:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct. To make matters worse, \Nit's quite a stable chemical compound.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:11.73,0:45:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, "It's quite stable"?
Dialogue: 10,0:45:13.89,0:45:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Dioxin is heat-resistant.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:16.40,0:45:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Acids, alkalis, and microorganisms \Nare unable to decompose it.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:20.11,0:45:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Once an area is contaminated,\N it will remain so for many years.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:24.32,0:45:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, once it enters the body, \Nit's almost impossible to remove.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:29.20,0:45:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens once\N it enters the body?
Dialogue: 10,0:45:31.79,0:45:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dioxin accumulates in the liver and kidneys,\N destroying their function.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:35.83,0:45:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, it degrades the immune system significantly.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:39.42,0:45:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You become defenseless\N to the slightest malady.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:42.05,0:45:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also believed to be\N a powerful carcinogen.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:45.01,0:45:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In many cases, after ingesting\N a lot of dioxin,
Dialogue: 10,0:45:47.80,0:45:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,people became seriously ill, \Nand some even died.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:51.97,0:45:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... as long as we keep on living here,
Dialogue: 10,0:45:54.48,0:45:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this deadly colorless and odorless\N poison will continue to affect us?
Dialogue: 10,0:46:00.02,0:46:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:31.18,0:46:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:42.36,0:46:46.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,That morning, they showed a detailed map \Nof the dioxin contamination.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:46.90,0:46:50.07,Overlap,,0,0,0,,{\an8}The contaminated area is divided \Ninto three zones: A, B, and R.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:50.62,0:46:54.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,The three zones were based on the wind direction on the day of the accident
Dialogue: 10,0:46:54.54,0:46:56.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,and the location of dead animals.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:56.91,0:47:02.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,Our house, as well as Lucio's, \NAnna's, and Grandma Sonia's,
Dialogue: 10,0:47:02.29,0:47:05.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,were located in Zone A,\N the most contaminated of all.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:06.59,0:47:10.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,Maria's house was in Zone B,\N with intermediate contamination.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:10.22,0:47:14.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,Enrico's and Angelo's houses were in Zone R, \Ndesignated as "caution required."
Dialogue: 10,0:47:16.48,0:47:22.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,{\t(4770,5770,\c&HD2C1C4&\3c&HD2C1C4&)}And then, they announced that\N Zone A had to be completely evacuated.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:32.24,0:47:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Why can't I take it?
Dialogue: 10,0:47:35.20,0:47:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He sat in the closet the whole time.{trusting OG TL here, although tana is "shelf; ledge; rack" and I don't see how you can be inside a shelf}\N There's no dioxin on him!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:39.62,0:47:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see,
Dialogue: 10,0:47:40.91,0:47:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll only allow us to bring one suitcase per person to the evacuation shelter.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:47.05,0:47:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Please bear with us for now, Marco.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:49.17,0:47:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll definitely come back here,\N and then you'll see him again.
Dialogue: 10,0:47:53.89,0:47:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But really, will they allow us\N to return here?
Dialogue: 10,0:47:57.06,0:47:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt!
Dialogue: 10,0:47:58.31,0:48:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've spent twenty years building this house!\N Where else could we go?
Dialogue: 10,0:48:03.06,0:48:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Even these windows.\N I made them bit by bit every weekend.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:06.86,0:48:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, and we had to repaint them twice.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:10.70,0:48:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We moved in here not long\N after Anna was born.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:14.57,0:48:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And then came Giulia, and Marco too.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:17.99,0:48:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. And with each one, \Nwe added a little to the house.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:22.75,0:48:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going anywhere!\N I want to stay here.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:27.46,0:48:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Marco!
Dialogue: 10,0:48:34.85,0:48:39.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,Thus, my family, as well as Lucio's \Nand the other inhabitants of Zone A,
Dialogue: 10,0:48:39.52,0:48:41.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,left our beloved homes.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:41.10,0:48:45.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,We moved to a hotel in Milan that\N the city had arranged for the evacuees.
Dialogue: 10,0:48:55.03,0:48:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's allowed in Zone A anymore?
Dialogue: 10,0:48:59.41,0:49:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I don't think we'll be gathering under that mulberry tree ever again.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:08.30,0:49:13.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ando, Enrico, and the others came to check on us at the Milan hotel for evacuees.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:13.97,0:49:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucio, Giulia, are you okay? \NYou don't seem well.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:20.02,0:49:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know,
Dialogue: 10,0:49:21.35,0:49:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sad because Anna's baby could have birth defects from the dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:28.44,0:49:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 10,0:49:29.98,0:49:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It hasn't been born yet. \NHow can you assume that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:49:33.57,0:49:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Similar defoliants were used\N in the Vietnam War.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:35.99,0:49:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Defoliants?
Dialogue: 10,0:49:37.45,0:49:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vietnam War began in 1961.\N It was a testing ground
Dialogue: 10,0:49:40.29,0:49:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for many new types of weapons, \Nincluding herbicides.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:43.66,0:49:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Defoliants and similar chemicals \Nwere widely used.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:47.50,0:49:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The lush jungle prevented the US military from locating the enemy,
Dialogue: 10,0:49:51.09,0:49:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so they sprayed huge amounts of defoliants over the area.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:53.92,0:49:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, they called it Agent Orange.
Dialogue: 10,0:49:56.93,0:49:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It made the jungle trees wither away,
Dialogue: 10,0:49:59.35,0:50:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but it also polluted the rivers and soil.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:01.52,0:50:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, when the war was over,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:04.18,0:50:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,many local inhabitants \Nwere affected badly.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:07.06,0:50:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Women exposed to it gave birth\N to children with deformed limbs,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:10.86,0:50:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or children lacking part of the skull.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:12.82,0:50:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of conjoined\N twins also increased.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:16.66,0:50:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But... it wasn't just the Vietnamese \Nwho suffered.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:19.82,0:50:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Returning American soldiers suffered from numerous inexplicable illnesses.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:26.16,0:50:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why this happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:50:27.96,0:50:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The defoliant they used contained the deadly poison dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:33.17,0:50:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This dioxin must be an invention of the devil.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:37.18,0:50:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If these man-made chemicals aren't handled properly,
Dialogue: 10,0:50:40.52,0:50:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they can cause very serious problems.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:47.02,0:50:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do about this? \NI can't come to a decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:51.11,0:50:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no way of knowing \Nif my child will be okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:50:53.82,0:50:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I won't give birth, then!
Dialogue: 10,0:51:00.82,0:51:04.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,Many women who had been exposed\N to dioxin during pregnancy
Dialogue: 10,0:51:04.29,0:51:08.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,decided to end their pregnancy by a surgical abortion.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:08.92,0:51:12.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,The government made a temporary exception for them.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:21.26,0:51:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Grandma Sonia.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:23.35,0:51:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Anna!
Dialogue: 10,0:51:24.68,0:51:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you feeling better?
Dialogue: 10,0:51:26.31,0:51:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for asking.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:27.77,0:51:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I've been moved to a Milanese hospital, I don't feel better at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:33.19,0:51:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Anna?
Dialogue: 10,0:51:36.19,0:51:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You look even sadder than me.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:40.49,0:51:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're worried about your unborn child, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:51:44.03,0:51:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:49.46,0:51:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor girl.
Dialogue: 10,0:51:52.08,0:51:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, you should be filled\N with happiness right about now,
Dialogue: 10,0:51:55.92,0:51:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead, you're faced\N with a terrible decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:01.34,0:52:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Anna, \NI want you to remember one thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:06.18,0:52:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,People make their way through life \Nby supporting one another.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:09.81,0:52:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what you decide, \Nor what happens in the future,
Dialogue: 10,0:52:14.19,0:52:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we would never let you \Nsuffer through it alone.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:20.65,0:52:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandma Sonia...
Dialogue: 10,0:52:23.57,0:52:27.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,A few days later, they reopened bus service to Zone B.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:29.16,0:52:32.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,We, the Seveso Detective Team, \Nmet at Maria's place
Dialogue: 10,0:52:32.96,0:52:36.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,to exchange our findings about dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:36.88,0:52:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, have you heard?
Dialogue: 10,0:52:38.17,0:52:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The ban on selling Seveso's{/made in ... vicinity} foodstuffs is understandable,
Dialogue: 10,0:52:41.26,0:52:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but now they extended it \Nto furniture and crafts too!
Dialogue: 10,0:52:44.59,0:52:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. My dad's factory was shut down, \Nso now he's unemployed.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:49.39,0:52:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's having a hard time.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:51.89,0:52:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They are finally waking up \Nto the full horror of dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,0:52:55.19,0:52:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You might feel healthy now,
Dialogue: 10,0:52:56.94,0:53:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's no telling \Nwhat'll happen in three months.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:00.07,0:53:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are suffering\N from chloracne.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:03.24,0:53:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Chloracne?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:05.32,0:53:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You get rashes all over your face and body.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:07.95,0:53:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Awful!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:09.62,0:53:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in that newspaper?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:11.04,0:53:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember how they made us \Ntake a blood test the other day?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:14.75,0:53:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The results are in here.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:16.96,0:53:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The article says that
Dialogue: 10,0:53:18.13,0:53:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,one-tenth of the people tested had\N a steep decline in their lymphocytes.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:23.51,0:53:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's so special about\N a decline in lymphocytes?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:26.39,0:53:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It undermines your ability \Nto resist illnesses.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:29.47,0:53:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Worse still, it increases your chances of developing leukemia.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:33.23,0:53:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 10,0:53:35.06,0:53:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What else is there?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:37.86,0:53:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly all the children from Zone A \Nhave a decline in lymphocytes.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:42.78,0:53:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:44.45,0:53:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So on top of losing our homes, \Nit screwed up our health as well?
Dialogue: 10,0:53:49.74,0:53:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I said "nearly all." That doesn't mean 100%.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:53.12,0:53:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you'll be all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:53:55.92,0:53:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy for you to say we'll be all right!
Dialogue: 10,0:53:58.33,0:54:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You live in Zone R. How can you understand how bad we feel?!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:03.34,0:54:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucio...
Dialogue: 10,0:54:14.14,0:54:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:15.85,0:54:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:54:17.02,0:54:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Anna?
Dialogue: 10,0:54:19.36,0:54:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The baby moved.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:21.36,0:54:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It just moved!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:23.61,0:54:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Our baby is alive!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:26.03,0:54:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In there, eager to start living!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:31.08,0:54:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonio, I will give birth to this child.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:34.20,0:54:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The possibility of birth defects\N won't stop me.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:37.42,0:54:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll live with the weight\N of the responsibility!
Dialogue: 10,0:54:42.96,0:54:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna,
Dialogue: 10,0:54:44.51,0:54:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever happens from now on, \NI'll do my best to protect our baby.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:53.52,0:54:56.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,Today, Mr. Ando gathered\N our Seveso Detective Team
Dialogue: 10,0:54:56.64,0:54:59.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,to share some of his shocking\N findings with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:54:59.52,0:55:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no exhaust trap tank in place?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:02.44,0:55:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, plants like ICMESA that produce dangerous chemicals
Dialogue: 10,0:55:07.11,0:55:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,have an exhaust trap tank\N after the safety valve.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:10.28,0:55:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if harmful substances were emitted in an accident,
Dialogue: 10,0:55:14.37,0:55:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they would end up trapped \Ninside that tank.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:17.29,0:55:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there was no exhaust trap tank \N at the ICMESA plant.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:22.79,0:55:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the dioxin that formed \Nin the reaction tank during the accident
Dialogue: 10,0:55:26.76,0:55:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was blown out into the air intentionally?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:29.88,0:55:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:31.47,0:55:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But why would they do that?
Dialogue: 10,0:55:33.26,0:55:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Adding a trap to every tank would cost a small fortune, I imagine.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:36.81,0:55:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn. This plant doesn't care at all\N about the people living near it.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:40.27,0:55:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They only care about\N fattening their wallets!
Dialogue: 10,0:55:43.02,0:55:44.98,TV,,0,0,0,,The dioxin that fell
Dialogue: 10,0:55:44.98,0:55:47.86,TV,,0,0,0,,on Seveso after the accident\N at the ICMESA plant
Dialogue: 10,0:55:47.86,0:55:51.07,TV,,0,0,0,,was detected in the soil\N down to depths of 25 cm.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:51.07,0:55:54.12,TV,,0,0,0,,The specialists say the soil contamination is of major concern.
Dialogue: 10,0:55:54.83,0:55:58.54,TV,,0,0,0,,The town of Seveso,\N inundated by dioxin from the sky,
Dialogue: 10,0:55:58.54,0:56:01.07,TV,,0,0,0,,has already been dubbed a "Chemical Hiroshima."
Dialogue: 10,0:56:02.04,0:56:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A "Chemical Hiroshima"?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:04.25,0:56:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroshima... Isn't that the Japanese city \Nstruck by an atomic bomb?
Dialogue: 10,0:56:08.80,0:56:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:10.68,0:56:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In Hiroshima, the atomic bombing claimed more than 100,000 innocent lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:17.47,0:56:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But it didn't end there.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:18.85,0:56:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who survived suffer to this day
Dialogue: 10,0:56:21.19,0:56:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,from leukemia and other\N radiation-linked conditions.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:24.31,0:56:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, it may have affected their children as well. {This is standard Japanese prejudice about the hibakusha. Studies showed no significant increase in birth defects in descendant generations.}
Dialogue: 10,0:56:28.07,0:56:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was just like Seveso.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:30.03,0:56:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't call it a "Chemical Hiroshima" for no reason.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:33.53,0:56:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:35.24,0:56:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must we put up with this injustice?!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:38.33,0:56:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not just talking about disease.\N Our homes too!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:41.33,0:56:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, we were happy that we finally found a decent temporary apartment.
Dialogue: 10,0:56:45.67,0:56:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, what do you think it was like?!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:48.09,0:56:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's next to another plant, \Nstinking all day long!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:51.05,0:56:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do the big shots put us \Nthrough all this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:53.72,0:56:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like they don't give a crap!
Dialogue: 10,0:56:55.51,0:56:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Does your father care about us at all?!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:00.10,0:57:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious that he cares?
Dialogue: 10,0:57:02.52,0:57:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why is he leaving us \Nto the whims of fate?!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:06.11,0:57:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father sits in his fancy chair, ignoring the suffering
Dialogue: 10,0:57:09.65,0:57:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we in Zone A are going through!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:12.61,0:57:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want him to do, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:57:14.99,0:57:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, perhaps we fared better than you did.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:18.91,0:57:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But we all live in Seveso.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:21.20,0:57:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We also know the terror\N of dioxin first hand.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:23.79,0:57:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The mayor is just a human being.
Dialogue: 10,0:57:25.88,0:57:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He can work infinitely hard, but he can only do so much, and he makes mistakes!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:30.51,0:57:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough, Enrico!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:31.97,0:57:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No more excuses about \Nyour dad's screw-ups!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:35.26,0:57:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?! I dare you to repeat it!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:37.10,0:57:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna fight?!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:37.76,0:57:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, Enrico! Let go!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:39.43,0:57:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, both of you!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:40.97,0:57:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand\N anything and never will!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:43.31,0:57:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only thinking about yourself!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:46.02,0:57:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that, you prick?!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:46.35,0:57:47.69,Overlap,,0,0,0,,That's enough, Enrico!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:47.19,0:57:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}You heard me!
Dialogue: 10,0:57:48.52,0:57:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:57:50.40,0:57:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this all happening?!
Dialogue: 10,0:58:02.12,0:58:03.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,The mayor is just a human being!
Dialogue: 10,0:58:03.96,0:58:07.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,He can only do so much, \Nand he makes mistakes!
Dialogue: 10,0:58:09.92,0:58:11.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,"Mistakes."
Dialogue: 10,0:58:12.55,0:58:14.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was wrong to say that.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:27.52,0:58:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:29.44,0:58:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrico.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:30.94,0:58:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still awake?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:32.23,0:58:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to talk with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:34.40,0:58:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,May I?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:35.65,0:58:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:37.28,0:58:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 10,0:58:39.28,0:58:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that after the incident,
Dialogue: 10,0:58:41.28,0:58:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you were told that the white powder\N was mixed with a highly toxic substance.
Dialogue: 10,0:58:45.04,0:58:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, is that true?
Dialogue: 10,0:58:48.79,0:58:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Roche said\N when I went there!
Dialogue: 10,0:58:51.09,0:58:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They said the mayor got an official notice!
Dialogue: 10,0:58:55.34,0:59:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true Roche told me that an extremely toxic substance had been mixed in.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:02.39,0:59:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why didn't you disclose it right away?
Dialogue: 10,0:59:05.56,0:59:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you hide vital information from the people?!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:09.15,0:59:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Lucio asked me:
Dialogue: 10,0:59:10.56,0:59:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"Does your father care about us at all?"{56:55}
Dialogue: 10,0:59:14.73,0:59:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I supposed to answer him?!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:18.99,0:59:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Roche...
Dialogue: 10,0:59:21.57,0:59:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Roche didn't tell me what\N the extremely toxic substance was.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:26.95,0:59:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I feared that if I made \Na public announcement quickly,
Dialogue: 10,0:59:29.83,0:59:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,without naming the substance,
Dialogue: 10,0:59:31.67,0:59:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd make the situation worse \Nby throwing people into a panic.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:36.67,0:59:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 10,0:59:39.22,0:59:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no right answer!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:45.56,0:59:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The real world is not \Nas simple as children think!
Dialogue: 10,0:59:51.81,0:59:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 10,0:59:53.65,0:59:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I may be a child, \Nbut I can understand that much.
Dialogue: 10,0:59:57.49,1:00:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,People come first! Politics and chemistry come after that!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:02.91,1:00:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If we forget that, there'll be even more incidents like this one!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:11.25,1:00:13.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,Two months after the accident.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:14.59,1:00:18.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,People began showing\N chloracne symptoms en masse.
Dialogue: 10,1:00:20.09,1:00:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts! It hurts!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:24.01,1:00:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Marco!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:25.43,1:00:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Marco... My poor... My poor son...
Dialogue: 10,1:00:33.23,1:00:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Who deprived Seveso of its peace?!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:36.27,1:00:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:37.82,1:00:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Who robbed us of our well-being?!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:40.78,1:00:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:42.11,1:00:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us back our homes!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:44.12,1:00:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Give them back!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:45.12,1:00:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Guarantee us a healthy life!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:47.54,1:00:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Guarantee!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:52.92,1:00:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this demonstration immediately!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:55.42,1:00:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone resisting will be arrested!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:57.71,1:00:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Demonstrating is our right!
Dialogue: 10,1:00:59.51,1:01:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You want us just to put up with it?!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:01.72,1:01:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the way!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:03.13,1:01:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrest them!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:06.01,1:01:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:07.31,1:01:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop right there!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:09.06,1:01:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you lay a finger on these people!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:11.80,1:01:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But Mayor...
Dialogue: 10,1:01:13.94,1:01:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:16.11,1:01:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These people have already had\N their share of undeserved suffering.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:36.04,1:01:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what'll become of us after this.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:40.59,1:01:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to return to my own home.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:44.47,1:01:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go there right now.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:45.84,1:01:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going too.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:47.85,1:01:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My cosmoses are probably starting to bloom already.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:50.64,1:01:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The saffron too. And the asters.
Dialogue: 10,1:01:53.60,1:01:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna go home!
Dialogue: 10,1:01:55.56,1:01:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:08.28,1:02:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, we're returning!
Dialogue: 10,1:02:37.56,1:02:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing has changed at all.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:48.16,1:02:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Marco will be happy too. {unsure what she means, likely the OG "I'll bring this to marko works just as well"}\NDon't you agree, dear?
Dialogue: 10,1:02:51.99,1:02:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. He'll be delighted.
Dialogue: 10,1:02:58.58,1:03:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful. They're blossoming\N just like last year.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:03.96,1:03:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As if nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:12.56,1:03:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you'd come here too, Lucio.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:16.23,1:03:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like something's out of place.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:19.19,1:03:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no different from before the dioxin fell.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:22.48,1:03:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I guess none of us will be able\N to run across those fields ever again.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:28.78,1:03:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not just here!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:30.16,1:03:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we're obsessed about dioxin,
Dialogue: 10,1:03:32.62,1:03:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we won't be able to enjoy running \Nall out, like we used to!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:37.25,1:03:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did it have to be us?! \NWhy did this happen only to us?!
Dialogue: 10,1:03:42.88,1:03:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, if you take that frustration out\N on Enrico, it won't change anything.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:48.80,1:03:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Complaining about it \Nto someone else is easy.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:51.47,1:03:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I think just talking \Nabout problems
Dialogue: 10,1:03:53.68,1:03:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same as running away from them.
Dialogue: 10,1:03:57.77,1:03:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we start blaming someone else,
Dialogue: 10,1:03:59.81,1:04:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,shouldn't we at least try to face the problem ourselves?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:08.61,1:04:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I really like\N to watch you run.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:13.16,1:04:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Aiming to be{addded} as fast as the wind, \Nas if trying to outrun yourself every time.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:19.75,1:04:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just from watching that, I could feel\N new strength emerging inside me.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:26.59,1:04:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Giulia...
Dialogue: 10,1:04:27.55,1:04:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucio, we'll run again. \NOne day, we will. I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 10,1:04:42.48,1:04:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Angelo? What happened?
Dialogue: 10,1:04:45.44,1:04:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Maria?!
Dialogue: 10,1:04:50.19,1:04:54.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's when we learned that Maria was showing symptoms of chloracne.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:13.97,1:05:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria, it's me. We're here to check on you.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:17.89,1:05:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Angelo and Lucio too. \NEnrico is here as well. Come on, Maria!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:22.85,1:05:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Go away.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:25.15,1:05:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want anyone to see me!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:28.40,1:05:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you, please go away!
Dialogue: 10,1:05:40.37,1:05:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Enrico?
Dialogue: 10,1:05:42.62,1:05:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, guys.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:44.71,1:05:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that I should apologize, somehow,\N to Maria, to you, to everyone.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:50.80,1:05:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The mayor...
Dialogue: 10,1:05:52.76,1:05:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad... My dad may have made a terrible mistake.
Dialogue: 10,1:05:57.93,1:05:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 10,1:06:00.01,1:06:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right after the accident,\N Roche gave my dad a clear warning
Dialogue: 10,1:06:04.60,1:06:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that an extremely toxic substance\N was mixed with the white powder.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:09.23,1:06:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,However, he decided to keep\N that fact to himself.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:12.82,1:06:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't know the exact chemical.\N He could only guess.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:15.57,1:06:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He feared an announcement \Nwould incite panic among the people.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:18.99,1:06:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's clear now that whatever data he had, \Nhe should've disclosed it sooner.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:25.12,1:06:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If he'd done that, we wouldn't have carried on heedlessly,
Dialogue: 10,1:06:28.08,1:06:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and dioxin wouldn't have gotten to us!
Dialogue: 10,1:06:31.21,1:06:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe Maria would've been spared too!
Dialogue: 10,1:06:36.59,1:06:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 10,1:06:38.22,1:06:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys, I'm truly sorry!
Dialogue: 10,1:06:44.27,1:06:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The dioxin fallout wasn't the mayor's fault.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:47.65,1:06:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't yours either.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:52.94,1:06:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I stood by and did nothing,
Dialogue: 10,1:06:55.53,1:06:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,except for taking it out on you \Nand running away from the truth.
Dialogue: 10,1:06:59.45,1:07:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But you... You faced reality head-on\Nand tried to fight it.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:03.58,1:07:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Enrico.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:05.70,1:07:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucio...
Dialogue: 10,1:07:08.42,1:07:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, \Ndioxin took its toll on all of us!
Dialogue: 10,1:07:12.59,1:07:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Seveso got smothered in dioxin \Nbecause of Roche!
Dialogue: 10,1:07:16.84,1:07:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't expose this,
Dialogue: 10,1:07:18.34,1:07:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,countless more tragedies \Nlike this one will occur!
Dialogue: 10,1:07:21.89,1:07:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get to work! We have to protect the future with our own hands!
Dialogue: 10,1:07:29.20,1:07:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A press conference?
Dialogue: 10,1:07:31.48,1:07:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Roche is meeting with\N the Milanese government tomorrow,
Dialogue: 10,1:07:34.69,1:07:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to negotiate compensation for the victims.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:37.57,1:07:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, Roche has invited journalists in for an official conference.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:42.53,1:07:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{I wonder }Who will be there for Roche?
Dialogue: 10,1:07:44.99,1:07:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably Chairman Söll and Partfogel.
Dialogue: 10,1:07:48.54,1:07:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The company's top brass, for sure.{yes, he says 'top class', but that's not right for English}
Dialogue: 10,1:08:11.10,1:08:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria, it's me, Angelo.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:14.82,1:08:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, we're all going \Nto the Roche press conference.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:18.53,1:08:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt I needed to let you know.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:23.28,1:08:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what'll come out of it,\N but I'll come again to tell you.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:31.21,1:08:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria!
Dialogue: 10,1:08:36.38,1:08:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My face... is hideous, isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,1:08:42.38,1:08:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I know...
Dialogue: 10,1:08:44.14,1:08:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We've decided to move\N away from Seveso.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:47.93,1:08:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad wants to go somewhere\N with no dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,1:08:52.19,1:08:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't want to leave everyone!
Dialogue: 10,1:08:57.40,1:08:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria...
Dialogue: 10,1:08:58.90,1:09:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I like you very much.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:02.11,1:09:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I will never forgive Roche\Nfor causing you so much pain.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:07.33,1:09:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Angelo...
Dialogue: 10,1:09:15.54,1:09:17.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,On the day of the press conference,
Dialogue: 10,1:09:17.84,1:09:21.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,a large crowd of Seveso inhabitants gathered in front of the venue,
Dialogue: 10,1:09:21.55,1:09:24.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,to protest to the Roche representatives.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:36.04,1:09:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the rear entrance is guarded.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:38.19,1:09:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it seems easier than the front.
Dialogue: 10,1:09:40.94,1:09:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}This way!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:42.95,1:09:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No admittance to the venue!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:45.02,1:09:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn back at once!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:46.70,1:09:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They damn well showered us in dioxin!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:48.99,1:09:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We got questions for this Roche guy!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:50.95,1:09:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! Let us go! Let us in there!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:52.79,1:09:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I said! No way!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:54.21,1:09:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's our chance!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:54.62,1:09:55.54,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Turn back!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:55.54,1:09:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Disperse right now!
Dialogue: 10,1:09:57.42,1:09:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us Roche!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:12.14,1:10:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,On the right, Partfogel from Givaudan.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:14.94,1:10:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On the left, Chairman Söll of Roche.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:17.90,1:10:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the press conference is\N hereby declared open.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:22.28,1:10:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me!
Dialogue: 10,1:10:24.24,1:10:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why exactly would you want
Dialogue: 10,1:10:25.82,1:10:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to produce a substance as dangerous as dioxin at your plants?
Dialogue: 10,1:10:30.70,1:10:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not in the least interested in producing a substance as troublesome as dioxin.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:36.12,1:10:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, among our products is a surgical antiseptic. Its production process
Dialogue: 10,1:10:41.30,1:10:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,requires a certain chemical called TCP.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:44.13,1:10:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, during the synthesis of TCP,
Dialogue: 10,1:10:47.72,1:10:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a negligible quantity of dioxin \Nis created as a byproduct.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:52.14,1:10:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Negligible quantity?
Dialogue: 10,1:10:54.77,1:10:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had an alternative to TCP,\N we'd be more than happy to use it instead.
Dialogue: 10,1:10:59.98,1:11:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, the hard reality is that there's no substitute.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:03.53,1:11:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you discover one, \Nbe sure to let us know first.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:07.45,1:11:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:09.78,1:11:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're saying, despite {knowing about }the risks, \Nyou had no choice but to use it?
Dialogue: 10,1:11:14.04,1:11:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case,
Dialogue: 10,1:11:15.08,1:11:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,shouldn't you have installed \Nall possible precautionary measures?
Dialogue: 10,1:11:18.96,1:11:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,According to my investigation, \Nthe reaction tank synthesizing TCP
Dialogue: 10,1:11:23.84,1:11:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was not equipped with an exhaust trap tank of any kind.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:27.34,1:11:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you tell us about that?
Dialogue: 10,1:11:31.39,1:11:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's... The thing is... You see...
Dialogue: 10,1:11:35.22,1:11:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This country's high court is currently deciding\Nwhether we are to blame in this situation.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:40.94,1:11:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dodging the question!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:42.31,1:11:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Weren't you just negligent, \Nslacking off on safety measures?!
Dialogue: 10,1:11:45.78,1:11:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:47.24,1:11:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The ICMESA plant had\N safety measures intended
Dialogue: 10,1:11:50.11,1:11:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to prevent overheating \Nin the reaction tank,
Dialogue: 10,1:11:52.87,1:11:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in particular, an emergency cooling system.
Dialogue: 10,1:11:56.41,1:12:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why didn't it operate this time, \Npreventing the accident?!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:01.04,1:12:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Regarding that, our internal investigation had shown that the worker
Dialogue: 10,1:12:04.17,1:12:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,controlling the cooling system made an operational error.
Dialogue: 10,1:12:07.34,1:12:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:08.92,1:12:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:11.05,1:12:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Giulia!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:12.97,1:12:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We went there and talked\N to the workers who were present!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:16.77,1:12:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The cooling system was supposed\N to operate automatically, but it didn't!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:20.44,1:12:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So it had to be activated manually, \Nby an emergency lever!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:25.40,1:12:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The workers didn't make \Nany operational mistakes!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:27.90,1:12:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The cooling system plainly failed to work,
Dialogue: 10,1:12:30.11,1:12:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because the company neglected the safety equipment!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:33.37,1:12:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my sister!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:34.41,1:12:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucio!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:34.87,1:12:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Giulia! Angelo!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:38.29,1:12:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrico!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:39.37,1:12:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What are children doing in here?
Dialogue: 10,1:12:41.58,1:12:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Who let them into the venue?
Dialogue: 10,1:12:43.33,1:12:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are those children?
Dialogue: 10,1:12:45.46,1:12:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, calm down, everyone! \NThey are the children of Seveso!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:50.09,1:12:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been on the front lines of dioxin from the start!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:52.93,1:12:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They're infinitely courageous!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:55.01,1:12:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I can testify to what they said \Nabout the cooling system malfunction!
Dialogue: 10,1:12:59.60,1:13:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 10,1:13:01.73,1:13:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any simple and precise answer \Nto the issue these kids just raised?!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:13.57,1:13:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This... We'll discuss this issue \Nonly after there's a verdict.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:17.24,1:13:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no answer for now.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:19.45,1:13:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do the trials prevent\N you from answering?!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:22.16,1:13:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you tell the truth,\N you'll undermine your position in court?!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:26.00,1:13:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No... The thing is...
Dialogue: 10,1:13:28.84,1:13:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't answer, \Nhere's another question!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:31.51,1:13:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Right after the accident,
Dialogue: 10,1:13:32.88,1:13:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you were aware that a large dose of dioxin had been released!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:36.85,1:13:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, you only warned the mayor about some vague, negligible risks!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:42.68,1:13:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you do that?!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:44.56,1:13:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dioxin lay thick on the ground.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:46.61,1:13:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How many days were you\N planning to hide that?!
Dialogue: 10,1:13:50.61,1:13:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's... It's unthinkable\N that we would hide anything.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:53.95,1:13:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You must understand that\Nanalyzing samples takes time.
Dialogue: 10,1:13:56.70,1:13:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lying again! The moment the accident occurred,
Dialogue: 10,1:13:59.99,1:14:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you already knew that dioxin had formed!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:03.08,1:14:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I don't understand\N what you're talking about!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:05.25,1:14:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It was unthinkable at the time \Nthat so much dioxin
Dialogue: 10,1:14:08.29,1:14:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,could form in a reaction like that!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:11.59,1:14:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop lying to us already!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:13.97,1:14:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize to the all the people of Seveso!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:16.47,1:14:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize right here!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:19.39,1:14:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We want at least an apology.
Dialogue: 10,1:14:21.31,1:14:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria is crying all day long!\N Apologize, you!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:29.31,1:14:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do something about them already!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:32.90,1:14:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:34.19,1:14:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hands off the children!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:36.28,1:14:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go! Stop it!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:38.24,1:14:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go! Let me go right now!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:40.41,1:14:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go! I haven't finished speaking!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:43.08,1:14:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it! Let us go! {minna wo? everyone?}
Dialogue: 10,1:14:45.87,1:14:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave me alone. Leave me alone!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:48.29,1:14:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it! Let me go!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:50.75,1:14:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Giulia... Enrico...
Dialogue: 10,1:14:53.38,1:14:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucio... Angelo...
Dialogue: 10,1:14:56.68,1:14:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,People are still suffering!
Dialogue: 10,1:14:58.18,1:15:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All because of dioxin! \NTheir sufferings will go on!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:01.10,1:15:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologize! Apologize, you!\N Apologize, I said!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:04.93,1:15:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This press conference is temporarily suspended!{no clue what's the first word honbajiro}\NThe conference is temporarily suspended!
Dialogue: 10,1:15:09.40,1:15:13.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,In the end, our cries fell on deaf ears.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:22.91,1:15:27.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,As usual, those men were concerned \Nwith their profits above all else.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:29.88,1:15:34.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,Companies that mass-produce goods, \Naiming to improve people's lives on a grand scale,
Dialogue: 10,1:15:34.63,1:15:37.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,are always built on the misery of other people.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:38.34,1:15:41.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,And that's not how it's supposed to be.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:43.39,1:15:44.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,But for me...
Dialogue: 10,1:15:45.31,1:15:46.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,For all of us...
Dialogue: 10,1:15:46.39,1:15:49.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,We finding convenience in abundant manufactured commodities.
Dialogue: 10,1:15:49.73,1:15:52.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,Would anyone say they'd prefer\N not to have them?
Dialogue: 10,1:15:54.94,1:15:56.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,Detergents that clean effortlessly,
Dialogue: 10,1:15:57.40,1:15:59.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,pesticides that protect crops from insects,
Dialogue: 10,1:16:00.53,1:16:03.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,various handy things \Nwe use in our everyday lives,
Dialogue: 10,1:16:03.91,1:16:05.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,all come from man-made chemicals.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:09.75,1:16:11.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,And that's not all.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:11.46,1:16:16.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dioxin also forms when vinyl and many other types of plastics are burned.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:16.92,1:16:20.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,The mountains of miscellaneous household waste piling up
Dialogue: 10,1:16:20.05,1:16:23.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,are yet another potential source \Nof dioxin emissions.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:24.93,1:16:27.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,We always seek greater convenience.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:27.60,1:16:29.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what if someone else...
Dialogue: 10,1:16:29.27,1:16:33.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,No, do we ever ask if we might become\N victims of our own devices as a result?
Dialogue: 10,1:16:35.11,1:16:40.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,The responsibilities we bear to the future \Nalways lie within ourselves.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:44.20,1:16:49.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,In February of the following year, \NGrandma Sonia passed away.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:54.25,1:16:55.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,And in March,
Dialogue: 10,1:16:56.71,1:16:59.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,Anna's daughter was born.
Dialogue: 10,1:16:59.42,1:17:01.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,A healthy, adorable little girl.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:02.68,1:17:07.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,Still, we didn't know whether dioxin might affect her in the future.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:07.93,1:17:12.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,Rather than dissipating, our anxiety\N about the child only grew after the birth.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:13.02,1:17:15.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,But at least one thing we know for sure.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:15.31,1:17:17.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,Whatever happens from here on,
Dialogue: 10,1:17:17.73,1:17:21.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,we won't let my sister and her baby \Nface difficulties on their own. {/won't leave ... to suffer alone}
Dialogue: 10,1:17:25.66,1:17:27.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,And so, a while later, it was time
Dialogue: 10,1:17:27.95,1:17:31.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,for the Seveso Detective Team to say goodbye.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:29.33,1:17:30.66,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Take care, Maria.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:30.66,1:17:32.08,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Maria, goodbye.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:32.08,1:17:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Maria.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:33.33,1:17:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I may be going away now, but I'm still a Seveso Detective Team member!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:37.21,1:17:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget me!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:38.38,1:17:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria, be sure to write to me!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:40.21,1:17:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Maria.
Dialogue: 10,1:17:42.76,1:17:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria! Maria! Maria!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:46.68,1:17:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Angelo, I'll never forget\N what you did for{/told} me!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:49.76,1:17:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you all!
Dialogue: 10,1:17:51.60,1:17:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 10,1:18:05.36,1:18:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Left already?
Dialogue: 10,1:18:07.37,1:18:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ando?
Dialogue: 10,1:18:09.53,1:18:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I'm going back to Japan.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:12.75,1:18:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is goodbye.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:14.37,1:18:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're leaving too? \NIt'll be lonely here.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:18.21,1:18:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The dioxin problem is not unique to Seveso.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:21.46,1:18:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan to work harder than ever in Japan \Nto ensure this tragedy never recurs.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:26.55,1:18:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I consider it my duty as a journalist.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:30.97,1:18:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you?
Dialogue: 10,1:18:32.35,1:18:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,For our part, we learned a lot\Nabout dioxin, thanks to you.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:37.31,1:18:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's clear as day. This terrifying man-made chemical
Dialogue: 10,1:18:40.65,1:18:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,will catch up with you, \Nno matter where you run.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:44.15,1:18:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to take a firm stance \Nand face it head-on.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:47.41,1:18:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for our own sake.
Dialogue: 10,1:18:50.91,1:18:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But even more, it's for the future\Nof this beautiful Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.64,1:19:18.02,Songs,,0,0,0,,It's sunny in most places
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.02,1:19:22.64,Songs,,0,0,0,,Only small areas are in shadow
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.44,1:19:27.74,Songs,,0,0,0,,In this frozen time
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.95,1:19:32.95,Songs,,0,0,0,,We pass the long summer day
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.37,1:19:39.00,Songs,,0,0,0,,Eucalyptus scents the air
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.83,1:19:44.55,Songs,,0,0,0,,Seeds are sown in the spring
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.26,1:19:49.84,Songs,,0,0,0,,The sun peeps through, glittering
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.76,1:19:55.27,Songs,,0,0,0,,On the road by the river
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.56,1:20:01.02,Songs,,0,0,0,,Unreachable voices
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.73,1:20:06.36,Songs,,0,0,0,,Thoughts that grow rusty
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.49,1:20:16.33,Songs,,0,0,0,,I chase a rainbow that won't disappear
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.33,1:20:24.67,Songs,,0,0,0,,A brand new day
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.67,1:20:29.72,Songs,,0,0,0,,Only starts now
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.34,1:20:35.39,Songs,,0,0,0,,For hundreds of millions of years
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.39,1:20:40.69,Songs,,0,0,0,,It's been the very same way
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.19,1:20:46.27,Songs,,0,0,0,,Repeating over and over again
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.27,1:20:51.32,Songs,,0,0,0,,What will happen this time?
